What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Active, Smart and Intelligent Packaging Market?

Market Analysis and Size

The active, smart, and intelligent packaging market employs innovative technologies to enhance product safety, shelf life, and consumer engagement. Plastic films with oxygen scavengers extend the freshness of packaged foods. Smart labels on paper packaging monitor temperature-sensitive pharmaceuticals. Glass bottles embedded with RFID tags track product authenticity. Corrugated board boxes equipped with moisture sensors prevent damage to electronics during shipping. Metal cans with freshness indicators ensure quality beverages.

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the global active, smart and intelligent packaging market, valued at USD 89.67 billion in 2023, will reach USD 152.92 billion by 2031, growing at a CAGR of 6.9% during the forecast period of 2024 to 2031. In addition to the insights on market scenarios such as market value, growth rate, segmentation, geographical coverage, and major players, the market reports curated by the Data Bridge Market Research also include in-depth expert analysis, geographically represented company-wise production and capacity, network layouts of distributors and partners, detailed and updated price trend analysis and deficit analysis of supply chain and demand.

